# Maestro CI cost (H25)

Runbook: `product-os/04-quality/maestro-ci-cost-runbook.md`

## Before pushing Maestro changes

**Mandatory (all agents and humans):**

```bash
cd apps/offline-product
npm run qa:maestro:prepush
```

**Before push on macOS (E2E / boot marker / flow changes):**

```bash
npm run qa:maestro:prepush:full
```

Do **not** push and poll GitHub as the first test loop — macOS runners are ~10× Linux minute cost.

## GitHub is confirmation, not discovery

| Do locally | Do on GitHub |
|------------|--------------|
| `qa:maestro:preflight` | Linux preflight (cheap) |
| `qa:maestro:prepush:full` (macOS) | macOS job only when iOS delta or not yet green on PR |
| `qa:maestro:golden-path:android` (optional) | Android emulator job (cost-gated) |

## Agent rules

- Run `qa:maestro:prepush` before every push touching Maestro paths
- Run `qa:maestro:prepush:full` on macOS when changing flows, boot anchor, or CI bootstrap
- **One push per fix** when possible — cost gate cancels superseded runs but each attempt still costs minutes
- Use `workflow_dispatch` on `offline-maestro.yml` for final full-matrix proof before merge
- Do not disable `maestro-cost-gate` or `cancel-in-progress` to “make CI pass faster”

## Merge gate

Both platforms green per `maestro-ci-cost-runbook.md` (iOS may be from an earlier PR commit if cost gate skipped macOS).
